The White House congratulates Uhuru Kenyatta on his election as president of Kenya and commends the people of Kenya for the peaceful conduct of the election. They also urge all Kenyans to peacefully accept the election results. The White House acknowledges the progress Kenya has made in strengthening its democratic institutions and encourages the implementation of political, institutional, and accountability reforms outlined in the Kenyan constitution. They emphasize the importance of Kenya upholding its international obligations, including those related to international justice. The United States reaffirms its commitment to its partnership with the Kenyan people, based on shared values of democracy, security, and opportunity.